ALL LINUX COMMANDS.

ls :- List all Directorys.
mkdir :- Create a directory.
ls -l :- Give all the details about Directorys which are avaliable.
pwd :- shows your current location.
touch :- to create a new file.
cd :- change directory (cd DevOps/).
cd .. :- one step back / exit current directory.
rm :- remove / delete the file.
rm -r :- remove / delete the directory.
rmdir :- remove / delete the folder.
cat :- too see the details inside the file.
zcat :- to se inside the zip file.
echo "write your message" > enter file name :- to store the message into selected fiel.
head :- to see the top 5 lines inside the file.
tail :- to see the last 5 lines inside the file.
tail -f :- to see the new updated lines.
less :-  lets you view a file page by page with navigation
more :-  shows a file page by page but with limited navigation.
cp <filename> <foldername>/ :- copy that file and pest in to selected folder.
cp -r :- copy the folder ans pest  in to selected folder.
mv :- move youre file one folder to another folder.
wc :- count the all words.
